An upset tummy can ruin your whole day. 
Many patients ask how they can assist with their stomach upset and nausea in a natural way. Fortunately, Mother Nature has given us Zingiber officinale, better known as ginger. 
Beyond its great taste, ginger contains many compounds that may assist with occasional stomach upset and nausea. Each ginger tummydrop is made from the purest and best tasting ginger. We use a special patent pending process to naturally enrich the beneficial compounds from ginger before adding it to each drop. The result? Tummydrops are unlike any other ginger you've tried before. Think of them as all of the goodness from a whole root of ginger concentrated into a single drop.

Suggested Use:
Adults, take up to 12 drops per day, or as directed by your physician.
Parents, keep out of reach of children. This is not a candy.
Medical guidelines recommend that you discuss this and all dietary supplements with your physician before use.
Made in a nut-free and gluten-free facility
Do not use if pouch is open or torn. Learn more, including full nutritional facts, at www.tummydrops.com

Methylfolate (5-MTHF) is the most biologically active form of folate in the human body. Unlike folic acid, it needs no enzymatic conversion within the body, and is therefore six times more bioavailable.

Many people suffer from a genetic disorder that prevents them from adequately converting folate into 5-MTHF. Since it does not require conversion, supplemental 5-MTHF quickly increases both blood and cellular levels of this critical nutrient.
In addition to its well-known role in supporting healthy fetal neural development, 5-MTHF is important in the synthesis of acetylcholine, an important neurotransmitter. 5-MTHF also supports a healthy cardiovascular system by helping to keep homocysteine levels within the normal range.
Homocysteine is a known risk factor for cardiovascular disease.
Quatrefolic is a registered trademark of Gnosis S.p.A.

As the flagship product in the RIVALUS lineup, PROMASIL combines seven powerful proteins to form a unique blend designed to provide muscles with a steady stream of amino acids over several hours – ideal for maximum muscle growth and muscle repair.

PROMASIL is nano-partitioned, a process where the product is both chilled and micro-filtered, preserving the macro nutrient profile and yielding exceptionally high bioactive protein fractions.

Additionally, microfiltration removes unwanted fats and sugars. Providing you with a very clean and exceptionally light tasting protein.
